00:00:22.040 --> 00:00:24.040
So, Jen, what is going
on here at this booth?

00:00:24.040 --> 00:00:26.940
JEN TONG: So behind us,
we see Project PANOPTES,

00:00:26.940 --> 00:00:29.730
which is an open source project
that includes open source

00:00:29.730 --> 00:00:31.380
hardware that is
composed entirely

00:00:31.380 --> 00:00:34.020
of commercial,
off-the-shelf components.

00:00:34.020 --> 00:00:36.000
And it is intended
to be low-cost enough

00:00:36.000 --> 00:00:37.860
for educational
institutions and hobby

00:00:37.860 --> 00:00:40.500
astronomers to build
these robotic telescopes

00:00:40.500 --> 00:00:41.925
and contribute to the project.

00:00:41.925 --> 00:00:43.800
TODD KERPELMAN: And so
what happens once they

00:00:43.800 --> 00:00:45.180
